The paper proposes a new learning scheme for off-policy reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper focuses on improving the performance of RL algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. The proposed scheme involves parallel learning and policy search, which is related to robotics and control (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses theoretical proofs of monotone improvement, which is related to optimization and control (cs.DC). Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics and Control), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.DC (Optimization and Control).
